description:
For sale: $1,090,000. A contemporary complete newly renovated (ceiling to floor),  brilliant sunshine in high floor apartment with 5 rooms (2 bedrooms), spacious layout, windows in every room makes this home very bright with a lot of sunshine, plenty of closets and cabinets, balcony facing the Manhattan and Brooklyn Bridges, stretching to Verrazano Bridge with partial view of East River and minutes drive to FDR (entry to north / south) and Route I-278. From the other side of this apartment, see the beautiful Empire State Building with its spectacular night lights view.
The apartment is in a wonderful condition but low maintenance with 50% of it is tax deductible. 

* Central split A/C (five separated units provides heat/cool air in every room and the kitchen);
* "City Quiet" double windows in bedrooms, enjoying quiet and nice shade;
* Luxury chandelier lights;
* Dimmer light control both in living Room and  2 bed Rooms;
* Molding decorated in living room, dining room and hallway;
* New hard wood floor installed in living room and 2 bed rooms; European luxury tile floor installed in dining room, kitchen, bath room and hallway;
* Contemporary new kitchen provides all new appliances: refrigerator, stove, kitchen ventilator, modern cabinets and granite counter top;  Kitchen open to the dining room directly;
* Spacious new bathroom with European style bathtub, shower and granite counter top.  Luxury and stylish tiles decorated the entire wall;
* Solid modern wood doors, five new closets all around the unit;
* New customer made heat radiator cover offering additional small cabinets for more convenient storage;
* Cable / Phone Line Is rewired and installed within the wall;

Building Amenities

* Parking lot is available 
* Laundry Room, Library Room, Bike Room, Common Storage and Lounge
* 24 hours Security Service and a video surveillance system
* Live-in Super
* Community Recreation Facilities
* Common Courtyard with Beautiful Garden around the S Shape Buildings
* Children?s Playground
* Pets Allowed  

Building is located in Civic center and very close to South seaport, Chinatown, Little Italy, City Hall, World Trade Center and Wall Street. Transportation is convenient which includes subway 4,5,6,N,R and bus M9, M15, M22 and M103. And the brand new Fulton subway station is just 10 minutes walk away which have 2,3,A,C,J,Z line. Grocery shopping is very convenient with C-Town supermarkets and 24 hours RiteAid and 24 hour Alibaba Deli store around the corner. There is also a Starbucks coffee store, Dominos Pizza, Fried chicken deli and liquor store nearby. Plenty of restaurants are within walking distance in Chinatown and Little Italy area. And for schooling, there are very good Gift and Talent School programs nearby at PS 124 and PS 130 with also a walking distance Catholic School from PK-8 around the corner. And excellent Stuyvesant High School is also closely reached by bus M22 within 12 minuets bus ride. Close by YMCA and Manhattan Youth Swimming center as well as Stuyvesant (open to public) Swimming center are also within 10-15 minuets bus ride. And parking space waiting list at this apartment is not that long in addition to many other private parking spaces around this area. Finally, a large Columbus Park with basketball, volleyball and soccer ball field is also one block away which also includes kids playground and a ping pong ball table too. So many, so many convenient ways to fill your daily life by living in this apartment. Finally, the maintenance fee is low after tax deductible exemption. 
Potential buyers, please call 718-818-0973 for an appointment. Thanks!
